CARE.   (A) IN GENERAL. The Secretary, in consultation 
with the Agency for Healthcare Research 
and Quality and the entity with a contract 
under section 1890 (a) of the Social Security 
Act, shall develop quality measures for use 
in the pilot program (i)  for episodes of care; and  (ii) for post-acute care. 

