readmissions. (iii) Rates of discharge to the community. 


 (iv) Rates of admission to an emergency 
room after a hospitalization. (v) Incidence of health care acquired 

infections. (vi) Efficiency measures.</p>

<p>(vii) Measures of patient-

centeredness of care.</p>

<p>(viii) Measures of patient perception 
of care.</p>

<p>(ix) Other measures, including measures 
of patient outcomes, determined appropriate 
by the Secretary. 
 (B) REPORTING ON QUALITY MEAS


URES. (i)  IN GENERAL. A entity shall submit 
data to the Secretary on quality measures 
established under subparagraph (A) 
during each year of the pilot program (in 
