<h3>SEC. 3201. PURPOSE. 
</h3>
<p>
The purpose of this title is to establish a national 

voluntary insurance program for purchasing community 

living assistance services and supports in order to</p>

<p>(1) provide individuals with functional limitations 
with tools that will allow them to maintain 
their personal and financial independence and live in 
the community through a new financing strategy for 
community living assistance services and supports;</p>

<p>(2) establish an infrastructure that will help 
address the Nations community living assistance 
services and supports needs;</p>

<p>(3) alleviate burdens on family caregivers; and  (4) address institutional bias by providing a financing 
mechanism that supports personal choice 
and independence to live in the community. 

